de.ityx.contex.itag

Class ModelPerformance

  • java.lang.Object
    • de.ityx.contex.itag.ModelPerformance
  • All Implemented Interfaces:
    Serializable

    public class ModelPerformance
extends Object
implements Serializable
    The ModelPerformance states the quality of an ITag model.
    The relevant measures are:
    • getDocumentPerformance(): the ratio of documents for which all required annotations have been predicted correctly.
    • ModelPerformance#getMultiTokenPerformance(): the ratio of required annotations for which all tokens or characters belonging to an annotation have been predicted correctly.
    • ModelPerformance#getTokenPerformance(): the ratio of tokens belonging to an annotation that have been predicted correctly.
    Each of these measures is described by the moments ModelPerformance.Moments.mean and ModelPerformance.Moments.variance, multi token and token performance provide these moments separately for each annotation type.

      • getPerformance

        public ModelPerformance.PerformanceTuple getPerformance(String label)
        The performance holds for each annotation or label type the moments obtained from evaluation. These are stored in ModelPerformance.PerformanceTuple.getMultiTokenPerformance() and ModelPerformance.PerformanceTuple.getTokenPerformance(). For ModelPerformance.PerformanceTuple.getMultiTokenPerformance(), these are ModelPerformance.Moments.mean and ModelPerformance.Moments.variance for the ratio of required annotations for which all tokens or characters belonging to an annotation have been predicted correctly. For ModelPerformance.PerformanceTuple.getTokenPerformance(), these are ModelPerformance.Moments.mean and ModelPerformance.Moments.variance for ratio of tokens belonging to an annotation that have been predicted correctly.
        Parameters:
        label - the label for which performance is to be retrieved.
        Returns:
        a tuple of ModelPerformance.Moments for the give label.
